description.narrative: The External communication, advocacy and partnership unit contributed to the Key results for children through a national summit with 100 traditional leaders. The celebrations of the 30th anniversary of the CRC was a major event this year, supported by the unit. With growing emergency, the External communication specialist and the team have organized many missions and interviews/documentary to advocate and put the situation in Burkina Faso back on the global agenda. A nationwide campaign “Ne M'Appelez Pas Madame" to fight against child marriage was a success, reaching 1 million population including adolescents and youth. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/02/2020
